title: Inner product on 2-vectors
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

An inner product on $$\T_p M$$ induces an inner product on $$\Lambda _2 \T_p M$$ via 
$$
\lang X\wedge Y, Z\wedge W \rang\coloneqq
\lang X,Z \rang \lang Y,W \rang - \lang X,W \rang \lang Y,Z \rang.
$$
The induced norm $$\|X\wedge Y\|$$ gives the area of the parallelogram spanned by $$X$$ and $$Y.$$